Following receipt of an application filed pursuant to KRS 304.38A-030, the commissioner shall review the application and notify the applicant of any deficiencies. The commissioner shall issue a certificate of authority to an applicant if the following conditions are met:
The applicant has verified to the commissioner that it has an initial minimum worth of at least two hundred fifty thousand dollars ($250,000);
The requirements of KRS 304.38A-030 have been fulfilled;
The individuals responsible for conducting the applicant's affairs are competent, trustworthy, and possess good reputations, and have had appropriate experience, training, or education;
The applicant is financially responsible and may reasonably be expected to meet its obligations to enrollees and to prospective enrollees. In making his or her determination, the commissioner may consider:
The financial soundness;
The adequacy of surplus, working capital, other sources of funding, and provisions for contingencies;
Any agreement for paying the cost of the limited health services or for alternative coverage in the event of insolvency of the limited health service organization; and
The manner in which the requirements of KRS 304.38A-030 have been fulfilled; and
Any deficiencies identified by the commissioner have been corrected.
